WEBVTT

00:00.148 --> 00:01.062
Hands up! Move away
from the radio.

00:01.106 --> 00:02.281
No harm's been done.

00:02.324 --> 00:03.673
You're under arrest.[ Grunts ]

00:03.717 --> 00:05.849
Unauthorized use
of government property.

00:05.893 --> 00:07.634
[Suspenseful music plays] Previously,
on "The Walking Dead"...

00:07.677 --> 00:09.288
Let them go.You'll have to pay

00:09.331 --> 00:11.638
for what you've done,
one way or another.

00:11.681 --> 00:13.466
Is this place really
as good as it seems?

00:13.509 --> 00:15.207
Better.If I wanted to get help

00:15.250 --> 00:16.947
for people,
I could do that here?

00:16.991 --> 00:18.862
As long as you follow
the rules.

00:18.906 --> 00:20.255
No, we're missing
something.

00:20.299 --> 00:21.909
Maybe they went
out the back.

00:21.952 --> 00:22.866
I can track 'em.

00:22.910 --> 00:23.824
Hold on.

00:23.867 --> 00:26.174
♪♪

00:26.218 --> 00:27.306
Told ya.

00:27.349 --> 00:28.524
♪♪

00:29.786 --> 00:32.920
♪♪

00:32.963 --> 00:35.096
Wait.

00:35.140 --> 00:38.404
Take a minute,
then we're almost there.

00:38.447 --> 00:40.058
About three miles out.

00:40.101 --> 00:41.885
Negan:
You can't be serious.

00:41.929 --> 00:44.149
Daryl just told us
to go home.

00:44.192 --> 00:45.672
I didn't hear that.

00:45.715 --> 00:47.369
Well, I think he was
being subtle.

00:47.413 --> 00:49.415
He said they were armed
with lookouts.

00:49.458 --> 00:52.113
And Daryl knows
I would never turn back.

00:52.157 --> 00:54.202
How're you gonna keep going,
Maggie, huh?

00:54.246 --> 00:57.684
With what army?

00:57.727 --> 01:02.036
Come on, Gabe,
back me up here.

01:02.080 --> 01:03.733
Our people
are about to starve.

01:03.777 --> 01:05.953
I'm not going back to my family
having failed.

01:05.996 --> 01:07.737
Oh, Jesus.

01:07.781 --> 01:10.740
At least admit what
you're asking of us --

01:10.784 --> 01:14.135
walking to our deaths for what,
a sack of beans?

01:14.179 --> 01:16.355
If you're more interested
in saving yourself

01:16.398 --> 01:19.445
than protecting
the people back home,

01:19.488 --> 01:20.837
you can go.

01:20.881 --> 01:22.578
[Birds chirping]

01:22.622 --> 01:25.059
We don't need you.

01:25.103 --> 01:26.843
We both know
that's not true.

01:26.887 --> 01:28.932
♪♪

01:28.976 --> 01:30.456
Alright,
tell you what.

01:30.499 --> 01:31.935
You make me
a promise --

01:31.979 --> 01:33.676
in front of
the goddamn preacher --

01:33.720 --> 01:35.069
and I will
stick around.

01:35.113 --> 01:36.853
Promise you what?

01:36.897 --> 01:38.507
I do this for you,

01:38.551 --> 01:41.336
and we're even,
we are good.

01:41.380 --> 01:44.034
I don't have to keep looking
over my shoulder.

01:44.078 --> 01:46.472
♪♪

01:46.515 --> 01:48.952
We will never
be even.

01:48.996 --> 01:50.258
Then you are gonna be down
a soldier

01:50.302 --> 01:52.042
that you
desperately need.

01:52.086 --> 01:53.914
Your call.

01:53.957 --> 01:59.354
♪♪

01:59.398 --> 02:01.617
You'd take a promise
from me?

02:01.661 --> 02:04.229
Really?

02:04.272 --> 02:07.014
Yeah.
Who wouldn't?

02:07.057 --> 02:10.365
I'm assuming you are
a woman of your word.

02:10.409 --> 02:12.628
I've always been
a man of mine.

02:12.672 --> 02:22.638
♪♪

02:22.682 --> 02:28.427
♪♪

02:28.470 --> 02:30.864
[Twigs snapping,
leaves rustling]

02:30.907 --> 02:32.909
What is it?

02:32.953 --> 02:34.694
[Walker growling]

02:34.737 --> 02:44.312
♪♪

02:44.356 --> 02:50.927
♪♪

02:50.971 --> 02:52.668
[Growling stops, body thuds]

02:52.712 --> 02:54.714
♪♪

03:03.026 --> 03:05.420
It's his sister's
best friend.

03:05.464 --> 03:07.292
Teresa.

03:07.335 --> 03:08.945
She was just a kid.

03:08.989 --> 03:12.732
♪♪

03:12.775 --> 03:14.777
We have to get them.

03:14.821 --> 03:18.128
[Walkers growling]

03:18.172 --> 03:20.305
All of them.

03:20.348 --> 03:23.699
♪♪

03:23.743 --> 03:26.224
Hey.

03:26.267 --> 03:28.051
Y'all know
Blackbeard, too?

03:28.095 --> 03:34.188
♪♪

03:34.232 --> 03:36.146
Wait.

03:36.190 --> 03:41.674
♪♪

03:41.717 --> 03:45.243
Think we can
find more?

03:45.286 --> 03:49.203
[Walker growling]

03:49.247 --> 03:59.213
♪♪

03:59.257 --> 04:09.223
♪♪

04:09.267 --> 04:19.233
♪♪

04:19.277 --> 04:29.243
♪♪

04:29.287 --> 04:31.680
♪♪

04:35.597 --> 04:39.688
[Walkers growling]

04:39.732 --> 04:49.524
♪♪

04:49.568 --> 04:50.873
♪♪

04:50.917 --> 04:55.487
[Panting]

04:55.530 --> 04:57.924
You're doing great.

04:57.967 --> 05:01.971
I'm doing okay,
not great.

05:02.015 --> 05:03.495
The timeline
since this was last

05:03.538 --> 05:05.323
an essential activity
in your daily routine

05:05.366 --> 05:06.759
and the necessity
for it

05:06.802 --> 05:09.196
should be factors
in your self-judgment.

05:09.239 --> 05:11.764
Stephanie: The military
does this for us.

05:11.807 --> 05:13.548
It's been so long
since I've had to.

05:13.592 --> 05:15.028
It's not like riding a bicycle,
turns out.

05:15.071 --> 05:16.334
You do forget.

05:16.377 --> 05:17.770
That's
the good ol' cerebellum

05:17.813 --> 05:19.424
protecting you from
unpleasant memories.

05:21.382 --> 05:23.602
I remember
the good stuff.

05:23.645 --> 05:30.086
♪♪

05:30.130 --> 05:34.569
Stephanie,
I-I have to ask.

05:34.613 --> 05:36.832
You've known Hornsby
a long time?

05:36.876 --> 05:38.921
Pretty long,
why?

05:38.965 --> 05:41.402
♪♪

05:41.446 --> 05:45.101
Is he capable of
taking care of our...

05:45.145 --> 05:47.408
transgressions?

05:47.452 --> 05:49.018
In other words,

05:49.062 --> 05:54.154
will all this labor
truly lead to our freedom?

05:54.197 --> 05:57.636
If he says it will,
it will.

05:57.679 --> 06:00.943
Lance has his own way
of doing things.

06:00.987 --> 06:03.511
But you
can trust him.

06:03.555 --> 06:05.470
You'll see.

06:05.513 --> 06:07.297
♪♪

06:07.341 --> 06:09.648
[Walkers growling]

06:09.691 --> 06:16.568
♪♪

06:16.611 --> 06:18.221
Whoa.
Let me take over.

06:18.265 --> 06:20.049
I got this.
I can help,
it's fine.

06:20.093 --> 06:22.748
No, it's not!
[Groans]
It will be.

06:22.791 --> 06:25.272
[Grunts]

06:25.315 --> 06:27.100
♪♪

06:27.143 --> 06:29.102
Ezekiel!

06:29.145 --> 06:30.843
What?

06:30.886 --> 06:33.585
I love you, but you got
to give me space, man.

06:33.628 --> 06:35.456
Can you just
clear these?

06:35.500 --> 06:37.676
[Gasps]

06:37.719 --> 06:40.113
[Groans]

06:40.156 --> 06:42.376
God!

06:42.420 --> 06:46.424
[Radio chatter]

06:46.467 --> 06:47.773
Think I got
the last of them.

06:47.816 --> 06:49.905
You okay?Yeah.

06:49.949 --> 06:51.646
Fine.

06:51.690 --> 06:53.431
Sorry, I didn't mean
to snap at you.

06:53.474 --> 06:54.910
It's just
so cramped in there.

06:54.954 --> 06:56.825
Nah,
it's cool.

06:56.869 --> 06:58.087
[Coughing]

07:01.830 --> 07:03.789
Ezekiel,
what can I do?

07:03.832 --> 07:06.269
It's --
It's dusty.

07:06.313 --> 07:07.619
[Sniffles]

07:07.662 --> 07:08.881
I'm sure that's it.

07:08.924 --> 07:11.492
Mm-hmm.
[Sighs]

07:11.536 --> 07:14.887
Y'all need help
clearing your area?

07:14.930 --> 07:17.019
Steph, how much longer
we got to do this?

07:17.063 --> 07:18.368
It's been days.

07:18.412 --> 07:20.806
Uh, a couple more,
I guess.

07:20.849 --> 07:22.155
He won't make it
a few more days.

07:22.198 --> 07:23.678
I'm fine.

07:23.722 --> 07:25.506
No, you need
to see a doctor.

07:25.550 --> 07:27.421
I'm not gonna leave you alone
to work out here.

07:27.465 --> 07:28.988
Don't be stupid!

07:29.031 --> 07:31.120
Yeah,
I said it.

07:31.164 --> 07:33.209
They got real hospitals
and shit here.

07:35.690 --> 07:37.953
Can you make
that happen?

07:37.997 --> 07:41.087
Uh, yeah, I'll talk
to Mr. Hornsby right now.

07:41.130 --> 07:43.393
Thank you.
We are much obliged.

07:45.178 --> 07:47.485
If this becomes another debt
we have to work off...

07:47.528 --> 07:49.530
Never been afraid
of hard work.

07:49.574 --> 07:52.577
Kinda anti friends who die
from stubbornness.

07:54.187 --> 07:56.885
[Walkers growling]

07:56.929 --> 07:58.800
Man: Mercer,
this is way too close to

07:58.844 --> 08:00.062
where the nasties
are working.

08:00.106 --> 08:02.978
The smell is...
revolting.

08:03.022 --> 08:10.464
♪♪

08:10.508 --> 08:14.163
Who the hell was that?

08:14.207 --> 08:17.645
Our recruiters were
incredibly impressed with you.

08:17.689 --> 08:19.168
Were they?

08:19.212 --> 08:21.040
I-I thought maybe
they found me difficult.

08:21.083 --> 08:22.563
[Chuckles]

08:22.607 --> 08:24.304
Well, we expect a person
with your pedigree

08:24.347 --> 08:26.088
to have
high standards.

08:26.132 --> 08:28.003
We certainly do
at State.

08:28.047 --> 08:29.962
♪♪

08:30.005 --> 08:32.312
Well, [Sighs] Ms. Milton
has great affection

08:32.355 --> 08:34.793
for her fellow
Harvard grads.

08:34.836 --> 08:37.012
Should be no trouble
finding a position for you.

08:37.056 --> 08:39.928
I'm happy to work to pay for
the aid for my community,

08:39.972 --> 08:42.583
but I'm not staying here
permanently.

08:42.627 --> 08:44.367
I just want
to make that clear.

08:44.411 --> 08:46.805
After you meet Ms. Milton,
you might reconsider.

08:48.981 --> 08:51.810
I'd rather
see my friends.

08:51.853 --> 08:53.115
Actually, can somebody
take me to where

08:53.159 --> 08:54.334
they're working,
please?

08:54.377 --> 08:56.597
They broke the law.

08:56.641 --> 08:58.381
Mr. Hornsby has arranged
for their release

08:58.425 --> 09:00.427
with a fine
that they're repaying.

09:00.470 --> 09:01.907
What?

09:01.950 --> 09:03.778
Yeah, I believe they're
clearing buildings

09:03.822 --> 09:05.606
for future development.

09:05.650 --> 09:08.087
Clearing them of what,
exactly?

09:08.130 --> 09:09.784
The dead.

09:09.828 --> 09:11.873
Okay, so they're assigned
to clear walkers

09:11.917 --> 09:14.484
for days, weeks?

09:14.528 --> 09:16.878
Months, maybe?

09:16.922 --> 09:20.142
And I'm expected to provide
legal services to --

09:20.186 --> 09:22.057
Ms. Milton
and her cabinet.

09:22.101 --> 09:24.407
Right.

09:24.451 --> 09:26.366
Then I'd like
to speak with her.

09:26.409 --> 09:28.977
Right away,
please.

09:29.021 --> 09:31.284
Well,
that would be difficult.

09:31.327 --> 09:33.025
Why is that exactly?

09:33.068 --> 09:35.418
It's just
Mr. Hornsby's expectations

09:35.462 --> 09:36.855
of the timing
were a little different.

09:36.898 --> 09:39.205
Is he
your supervisor?

09:39.248 --> 09:40.772
No.

09:40.815 --> 09:43.862
Then I'd like to speak to her
right away.

09:43.905 --> 09:45.646
Please.

09:49.781 --> 09:51.347
Come on, boy.[Dog woofs]

09:51.391 --> 09:52.740
[Dog panting]

09:52.784 --> 09:56.048
[Rope creaking]

10:07.233 --> 10:08.800
You need
any help in there?

10:08.843 --> 10:10.584
No.

10:18.984 --> 10:20.463
You want one?

10:20.507 --> 10:22.117
Sure.

10:23.684 --> 10:25.730
Here you go.

10:25.773 --> 10:28.602
Thanks.

10:28.646 --> 10:31.170
[Match strikes]

10:31.213 --> 10:34.086
♪♪

10:34.129 --> 10:36.131
Man:
Here they come!

10:36.175 --> 10:38.133
Open up!

10:38.177 --> 10:40.919
On it, on it!

10:40.962 --> 10:43.008
Sounds like patrol
has come home.

10:43.051 --> 10:44.270
Yo, let them in.
Yep.

10:44.313 --> 10:47.577
[Walker growling]

10:47.621 --> 10:51.538
♪♪

10:51.581 --> 10:53.975
Blessed are the dead
who die in the Lord,

10:54.019 --> 10:58.893
even so saith the Spirit,
for they rest from their labors.

10:58.937 --> 11:02.505
We say, "The Lord be with you
and thy Spirit."

11:02.549 --> 11:05.117
Amen.Amen.
Amen.Amen.

11:05.160 --> 11:08.773
If your sister's out there,
we'll find her.

11:08.816 --> 11:11.950
♪♪

11:11.993 --> 11:15.214
And every last one
of these murderers.

11:15.257 --> 11:18.478
All of them.

11:18.521 --> 11:22.612
But the one --
he's mine.

11:22.656 --> 11:27.356
♪♪

11:27.400 --> 11:30.664
[Knife scraping]

11:30.708 --> 11:32.144
♪♪

11:32.187 --> 11:35.495
[Sighs]

11:35.538 --> 11:42.981
♪♪

11:43.024 --> 11:44.765
There are
scouts everywhere.

11:44.809 --> 11:46.767
I'll be careful.

11:46.811 --> 11:50.162
If you get a chance
to kill one of them,

11:50.205 --> 11:53.339
if he's alone
and you have the advantage...

11:53.382 --> 11:54.993
I will.

11:55.036 --> 11:59.475
♪♪

11:59.519 --> 12:01.913
[Sighs]

12:01.956 --> 12:04.872
[Growling continues]

12:04.916 --> 12:06.569
You ready?

12:06.613 --> 12:10.225
I'm not cutting up
anyone I know.

12:10.269 --> 12:13.054
You're gonna have to find me
four strangers.

12:13.098 --> 12:15.448
Only need three.

12:15.491 --> 12:18.538
I kept my mask for practical
and sentimental reasons.

12:18.581 --> 12:20.148
This is not fun.

12:20.192 --> 12:23.499
Well,
not with that attitude.

12:23.543 --> 12:24.892
Let's get it
over with.

12:24.936 --> 12:27.808
[Chuckles]

12:27.852 --> 12:37.818
♪♪

12:37.862 --> 12:40.865
♪♪

12:42.431 --> 12:44.825
We did
three different sweeps.

12:44.869 --> 12:46.871
No signs of tracks
anywhere, sir.

12:49.003 --> 12:50.788
You try the buildings
out by the lake?

12:50.831 --> 12:52.267
Yes, sir.

12:52.311 --> 12:54.139
Along the train tracks?Yes, sir.

12:54.182 --> 12:56.184
Freeway underpasses?

12:56.228 --> 12:57.882
Yes, sir.Oh, come on!

12:57.925 --> 13:00.710
There are dozens of
these assholes out there!

13:00.754 --> 13:02.756
Pope.
No!

13:02.800 --> 13:08.849
♪♪

13:08.893 --> 13:10.895
Your brothers
are dead!

13:10.938 --> 13:13.767
♪♪

13:13.811 --> 13:17.075
Are you not ashamed?!

13:17.118 --> 13:20.687
Or do you think
this is acceptable?!

13:20.730 --> 13:23.255
They were following
my recommendations.

13:23.298 --> 13:25.039
I told them where
the last teams went.

13:25.083 --> 13:28.042
I told them
where to go next.

13:28.086 --> 13:29.565
You want to scream
at somebody,

13:29.609 --> 13:32.612
scream at me.

13:32.655 --> 13:34.005
You trying
to be noble?

13:34.048 --> 13:37.225
Is that it,
Shaw?

13:37.269 --> 13:41.403
You trying to get them
to like you?

13:41.447 --> 13:44.102
Try keeping them alive.

13:44.145 --> 13:46.147
And yelling at them
is gonna do that?

13:46.191 --> 13:56.157
♪♪

13:56.201 --> 13:59.769
♪♪

13:59.813 --> 14:02.860
Go be useful.

14:02.903 --> 14:04.687
Take your boy
over there

14:04.731 --> 14:07.952
and go and find
my goddamn enemies!

14:07.995 --> 14:17.875
♪♪

14:17.918 --> 14:19.964
Come on.
We have orders.

14:20.007 --> 14:21.269
♪♪

14:21.313 --> 14:23.968
[Dog panting]

14:24.011 --> 14:25.273
Stay.

14:28.973 --> 14:30.409
[Geese honking]

14:30.452 --> 14:32.106
Daryl:
You alright?

14:32.150 --> 14:34.630
I'm fine.

14:34.674 --> 14:37.720
♪♪

14:37.764 --> 14:40.158
I'm sure
the guys are grateful

14:40.201 --> 14:42.421
for what you did
back there.

14:42.464 --> 14:44.379
How do you
know that?

14:44.423 --> 14:46.207
I'd be.

14:46.251 --> 14:48.035
I don't know.

14:48.079 --> 14:49.645
It may have been
stupid.

14:49.689 --> 14:51.734
No,
you got a good place.

14:51.778 --> 14:53.954
I'm sure there's a good story
that goes with it.

14:53.998 --> 14:56.304
Well, you spent some time
with those people.

14:56.348 --> 14:58.263
I'm sure
they have their sides.

14:58.306 --> 15:00.395
No,
not at all.

15:00.439 --> 15:03.224
Well,
we needed a place.

15:03.268 --> 15:04.704
We found one.

15:04.747 --> 15:06.662
You can
fill in the rest.

15:06.706 --> 15:10.971
♪♪

15:11.015 --> 15:12.538
You got something
to say about it?

15:12.581 --> 15:14.061
No.
I'm just surprised is all.

15:14.105 --> 15:16.890
Surprised why?

15:16.934 --> 15:18.370
You won.

15:18.413 --> 15:20.894
You got the walls.
You got the food.

15:20.938 --> 15:23.201
Why keep hunting?

15:23.244 --> 15:26.639
We have to make sure
they don't come back.

15:26.682 --> 15:28.771
Okay.

15:28.815 --> 15:30.599
You know,
you don't understand.

15:30.643 --> 15:32.340
It's easy for you
out here on your own,

15:32.384 --> 15:33.994
only having to worry
about yourself.

15:34.038 --> 15:36.736
We have a whole community
to protect.

15:36.779 --> 15:38.738
And we have
a structure.

15:38.781 --> 15:41.306
And a leader
who got us this far.

15:41.349 --> 15:42.611
What happened
back there --

15:42.655 --> 15:44.787
that was --
that wasn't normal.

15:44.831 --> 15:47.442
Yeah, I met guys
like that before.

15:47.486 --> 15:50.663
Pope's got a puzzle to solve,
and he's riled up.

15:50.706 --> 15:53.405
♪♪

15:53.448 --> 15:55.668
How can these people
be so hard to find?

15:55.711 --> 15:59.324
♪♪

15:59.367 --> 16:01.065
So,
you kill everybody,

16:01.108 --> 16:02.980
and then he goes back
to being a good guy?

16:03.023 --> 16:04.807
He's like
a father to me.

16:04.851 --> 16:07.462
He believed in me
when no one else would.

16:07.506 --> 16:09.203
He made me strong.

16:09.247 --> 16:11.901
I doubt you ever needed anyone
to make you strong.

16:11.945 --> 16:20.388
♪♪

16:20.432 --> 16:23.696
[Walkers growling]

16:23.739 --> 16:33.706
♪♪

16:33.749 --> 16:41.018
♪♪

16:41.061 --> 16:43.498
Negan:
Lower your shoulders.

16:43.542 --> 16:46.588
Arms limp.

16:46.632 --> 16:48.373
That's good,
Maggie.

16:48.416 --> 16:51.419
[Growling continues]

16:51.463 --> 17:01.429
♪♪

17:01.473 --> 17:11.439
♪♪

17:11.483 --> 17:21.449
♪♪

17:21.493 --> 17:29.457
♪♪

17:29.501 --> 17:31.242
Back to the tree.

17:31.285 --> 17:34.245
[Growling continues]

17:34.288 --> 17:35.898
This piece of shit.

17:35.942 --> 17:37.509
[Chuckles]

17:37.552 --> 17:39.859
It's not gonna
fit you perfectly.

17:39.902 --> 17:43.906
It was...
someone else's face.

17:43.950 --> 17:47.127
Look,
this might actually work.

17:47.171 --> 17:48.389
And I mean it.

17:48.433 --> 17:51.044
If I can do it,
you can do it.

17:51.088 --> 17:52.654
I'll take this back,

17:52.698 --> 17:54.874
work on it,
fix it for you.

17:54.917 --> 17:57.050
Then we'll
try it again.

17:57.094 --> 17:59.008
You did good,
Maggie.

18:00.532 --> 18:03.361
[Sighs]

18:12.283 --> 18:22.249
♪♪

18:22.293 --> 18:32.259
♪♪

18:32.303 --> 18:41.573
♪♪

18:41.616 --> 18:45.925
[Whispering indistinctly]

18:45.968 --> 18:49.189
Blessed are they
who die in the Lord,

18:49.233 --> 18:51.583
so saith the Spirit.

18:51.626 --> 18:56.022
Blessed are they
who die in the Lord,

18:56.065 --> 18:59.721
so saith the Spirit,
for they rest from their labors.

18:59.765 --> 19:01.897
Blessed are they who --

19:01.941 --> 19:11.907
♪♪

19:11.951 --> 19:21.917
♪♪

19:21.961 --> 19:24.920
♪♪

19:24.964 --> 19:27.271
Tell me, Father.

19:27.314 --> 19:32.406
♪♪

19:32.450 --> 19:35.670
You have guided me
through the darkest of times.

19:35.714 --> 19:37.933
♪♪

19:37.977 --> 19:42.590
I treasure our conversation and
the guidance you have given me.

19:42.634 --> 19:44.679
Is there anything I should know?

19:44.723 --> 19:54.689
♪♪

19:54.733 --> 19:56.517
♪♪

19:56.561 --> 19:58.693
Thank you, Father.

20:04.786 --> 20:06.440
[Indistinct conversations]

20:06.484 --> 20:09.095
Man: Enlist in
the Commonwealth Army today.

20:09.138 --> 20:10.705
Help protect --How long is your break?

20:10.749 --> 20:12.533
Not long.

20:12.577 --> 20:15.667
Just enough to show you
my dorm room and then get back.

20:15.710 --> 20:17.843
You've always lived
in a dorm here?

20:17.886 --> 20:19.323
[Laughing]
Yeah. It's great.

20:19.366 --> 20:21.281
Tomi,
I'm sorry.

20:21.325 --> 20:23.283
I-I just don't understand
why you wouldn't want the life

20:23.327 --> 20:25.851
that comes along
with being a doctor here.

20:25.894 --> 20:28.245
I don't want to go back
to before.

20:28.288 --> 20:29.681
Well,
it wouldn't be the same.

20:29.724 --> 20:31.117
Dad isn't here
to put pressure on you.

20:31.160 --> 20:32.901
It wasn't just Dad.

20:32.945 --> 20:35.687
And you liked that type of life,
but I didn't.

20:35.730 --> 20:38.037
Never turning it off,
never sleeping,

20:38.080 --> 20:40.692
everything moving
too fast.

20:40.735 --> 20:42.259
People who burn themselves out
for work

20:42.302 --> 20:44.304
until they die
or want to?

20:44.348 --> 20:46.306
Do your part
to keep our community safe.

20:46.350 --> 20:48.787
[Sighs]Hey, you used to love
the job.

20:48.830 --> 20:52.007
I remember how you used to look
when you saved someone,

20:52.051 --> 20:53.487
when you told somebody
good news.
Please stop.
Please stop.

20:53.531 --> 20:54.749
That's the Commonwealth way.

20:54.793 --> 20:57.317
Sit.

20:57.361 --> 21:01.930
♪♪

21:01.974 --> 21:04.803
No one can know
that I was a doctor, okay?

21:04.846 --> 21:06.631
Promise me.

21:06.674 --> 21:10.112
What does thatmean?Just trust me,
okay?

21:10.156 --> 21:12.506
[Sighs]

21:12.550 --> 21:15.640
I like things
the way they are.

21:15.683 --> 21:17.555
This place makes sense.

21:17.598 --> 21:18.991
There's order,
a system --
Okay!

21:19.034 --> 21:20.775
Okay.

21:20.819 --> 21:22.734
Fine.

21:22.777 --> 21:25.258
Enlist in
the Commonwealth Army today.

21:25.302 --> 21:28.653
Help protect your neighbors
and defend our home.[Sighs]

21:28.696 --> 21:31.351
Remember, we're all
in this together.

21:31.395 --> 21:34.659
I have a meeting
with Pamela Milton later.

21:34.702 --> 21:37.009
Anything I should know?

21:37.052 --> 21:38.706
♪♪

21:38.750 --> 21:40.969
[Chuckles]
That's nice for you.

21:41.013 --> 21:43.363
Someone like me
would never meet Ms. Milton.

21:43.407 --> 21:45.104
Why not?

21:45.147 --> 21:48.586
You have to know
your place.

21:48.629 --> 21:50.109
You.Hey, whoa, whoa!

21:50.152 --> 21:51.328
Hey! Hey!
What do you think
I did?

21:51.371 --> 21:52.590
I did nothing wrong,
I swear.

21:52.633 --> 21:54.505
Hey! Stop!
I'm his lawyer.

21:54.548 --> 21:55.854
He's entitled to hear
his rights.Miko, Miko, no.

21:55.897 --> 21:57.769
Miko, leave it alone.Come on. Move it.

21:57.812 --> 21:59.945
That's the Commonwealth way.

22:04.645 --> 22:07.909
[Walkers growling]

22:07.953 --> 22:17.919
♪♪

22:17.963 --> 22:27.929
♪♪

22:27.973 --> 22:29.975
♪♪

22:38.984 --> 22:40.681
[Sighs]

22:40.725 --> 22:43.771
♪♪

22:43.815 --> 22:46.600
I told you
you'd get it right.

22:46.644 --> 22:49.124
Congrats
and you're welcome.

22:49.168 --> 22:54.521
♪♪

22:54.565 --> 22:56.480
Has he changed?

22:56.523 --> 23:01.398
♪♪

23:01.441 --> 23:02.921
[Sighs]

23:02.964 --> 23:05.097
We can't know that.

23:05.140 --> 23:08.100
♪♪

23:08.143 --> 23:10.537
He's helpful.

23:10.581 --> 23:12.104
He would be,

23:12.147 --> 23:16.151
long as there's
something in it for him.

23:16.195 --> 23:18.023
So,
your promise?

23:18.066 --> 23:21.983
♪♪

23:22.027 --> 23:24.333
I hope
I can keep it.

23:24.377 --> 23:28.163
♪♪

23:28.207 --> 23:31.471
You know, keep an eye open
for which one you want,

23:31.515 --> 23:33.560
because as soon as we restock,
you've got first dibs.

23:33.604 --> 23:35.606
Hey!
I need to talk to you.

23:35.649 --> 23:39.697
[Radio chatter]

23:39.740 --> 23:41.786
Where the hell
is my brother?
He's fine.

23:41.829 --> 23:44.832
That wasn't
my question.

23:44.876 --> 23:47.052
You made an appointment
with Pamela,

23:47.095 --> 23:48.270
even after I told you
and your friends

23:48.314 --> 23:50.272
that I was
taking care of things.

23:50.316 --> 23:52.057
You almost
screwed everything up.

23:52.100 --> 23:54.494
You kidnapped my brother
off the street.

23:54.538 --> 23:56.148
Fair enough.

23:56.191 --> 23:58.280
He'll be home tonight.
That's how much time I need.

23:58.324 --> 24:00.500
For what?

24:00.544 --> 24:03.460
Alright, it works like this.
It's real simple.

24:03.503 --> 24:05.244
Your people need help,
right?

24:05.287 --> 24:06.593
And you
want your friends,

24:06.637 --> 24:09.422
who broke the law,
to go free.

24:09.466 --> 24:12.251
Those are big asks.

24:12.294 --> 24:15.297
I can deliver
for you.

24:15.341 --> 24:17.517
There must be
something in it for you.

24:17.561 --> 24:20.651
♪♪

24:20.694 --> 24:23.262
A friend
in high places.

24:23.305 --> 24:24.916
Someday,
I might need a favor,

24:24.959 --> 24:30.661
and you might be
favorably inclined.

24:30.704 --> 24:32.140
So what do you say?

24:32.184 --> 24:34.273
Can you sit tight
for a few more hours?

24:34.316 --> 24:37.624
♪♪

24:37.668 --> 24:39.365
A few hours.

24:39.408 --> 24:41.410
Excellent.

24:41.454 --> 24:45.371
♪♪

24:45.414 --> 24:48.635
[Birds chirping]

24:48.679 --> 24:58.645
♪♪

24:58.689 --> 25:01.387
♪♪

25:01.430 --> 25:03.084
Hey.

25:03.128 --> 25:07.349
♪♪

25:07.393 --> 25:09.351
Patrol has been
all through here.

25:09.395 --> 25:11.092
They've checked every building
for miles.

25:11.136 --> 25:13.225
These trails
should be cold.

25:13.268 --> 25:16.184
♪♪

25:16.228 --> 25:19.231
Well, it looks like
someone's been through here.

25:19.274 --> 25:21.233
Heads up.

25:21.276 --> 25:30.198
♪♪

25:30.242 --> 25:31.504
♪♪

25:31.548 --> 25:34.463
Come out!
Hands up.

25:34.507 --> 25:37.336
♪♪

25:37.379 --> 25:39.599
Please,
don't shoot.

25:39.643 --> 25:41.645
I-I-I have a family
who needs me.

25:41.688 --> 25:43.124
Please.

25:43.168 --> 25:45.605
You staying
over there?

25:45.649 --> 25:48.434
No.How'd you avoid
the patrols?

25:48.477 --> 25:50.218
What?

25:50.262 --> 25:52.090
There's been soldiers
looking for people like you.

25:52.133 --> 25:53.526
How'd you avoid them?

25:53.570 --> 25:54.875
I-I don't know
what that means.

25:54.919 --> 25:56.224
Then you're of
no use to us.

25:56.268 --> 25:57.617
You don't know
what we've been through.

25:57.661 --> 25:59.314
My wife
is hurt real bad.

25:59.358 --> 26:02.187
I can't -- I can't care for her
and look for food.

26:02.230 --> 26:04.711
Please just --
just let me go.

26:04.755 --> 26:09.847
Show us or I'll shoot
and find your family later.

26:09.890 --> 26:11.326
Okay.

26:11.370 --> 26:14.068
Just please
don't hurt us.

26:14.112 --> 26:16.505
Move.

26:16.549 --> 26:18.116
♪♪

26:18.159 --> 26:20.422
Shaw to Pope.

26:20.466 --> 26:21.815
Hold up.
Pope:
Go ahead, Shaw.

26:21.859 --> 26:23.861
We found a man
in the woods.

26:23.904 --> 26:25.384
Not sure if he's a part
of our targets.

26:25.427 --> 26:26.820
He's taking us
to his people.

26:26.864 --> 26:29.344
How do you
want us to engage?

26:29.388 --> 26:31.433
Pope:
Kill them.

26:31.477 --> 26:34.088
♪♪

26:34.132 --> 26:36.743
Copy that.

26:36.787 --> 26:38.223
Daryl: Move.

26:42.706 --> 26:46.753
[Walkers growling]

26:46.797 --> 26:56.763
♪♪

26:56.807 --> 27:06.773
♪♪

27:06.817 --> 27:11.691
♪♪

27:11.735 --> 27:15.042
You know, I feel for you
in all of this.

27:15.086 --> 27:17.392
You might think
that's bullshit,

27:17.436 --> 27:19.786
but it's true.

27:19.830 --> 27:22.615
How's that?

27:22.659 --> 27:24.312
I'm not a robot,
Rhee.

27:24.356 --> 27:28.012
It sucks to see your friends
as walkers.

27:28.055 --> 27:32.103
And that would
be enough.

27:32.146 --> 27:34.148
But you are about to do
some crazy shit

27:34.192 --> 27:37.369
and break into a community
that you built and lost.

27:37.412 --> 27:39.153
♪♪

27:39.197 --> 27:40.807
I get it.

27:40.851 --> 27:43.070
Your community
and mine

27:43.114 --> 27:45.290
were lost
in very different ways.

27:45.333 --> 27:46.813
You think
I don't understand

27:46.857 --> 27:49.337
the losing side
of a massacre?

27:49.381 --> 27:52.993
There were no children
at the satellite station.

27:53.037 --> 27:55.692
No families.

27:55.735 --> 27:57.345
Then where'd Aaron
get Gracie?

27:57.389 --> 28:01.088
♪♪

28:01.132 --> 28:03.351
You think I don't know
about that?

28:03.395 --> 28:07.225
You can't debate battle plans
with me.

28:07.268 --> 28:08.748
Levels of cruelty.

28:08.792 --> 28:10.750
Look, all I'm saying
is that I remember

28:10.794 --> 28:14.711
when my home was invaded
and my people were killed.

28:14.754 --> 28:18.889
Those men --
they had friends.

28:18.932 --> 28:21.152
They had girlfriends.

28:21.195 --> 28:26.766
People that felt a loss
that I couldn't heal.

28:26.810 --> 28:30.552
And I had to explain
to them why --

28:30.596 --> 28:34.165
why their leader failed
to protect them.

28:34.208 --> 28:36.428
You killed people
who had families.

28:36.471 --> 28:39.997
♪♪

28:40.040 --> 28:42.782
And you did it
in front of their families.

28:42.826 --> 28:45.002
Yeah.

28:45.045 --> 28:47.178
I did.

28:47.221 --> 28:51.356
But the world is different now,
Maggie.

28:51.399 --> 28:55.577
Fewer people to fight for,
fight with.

28:55.621 --> 28:57.666
Hell, there's fewer things
to fight over.

28:57.710 --> 29:01.801
♪♪

29:01.845 --> 29:04.021
Are you saying
you'd do things differently?

29:04.064 --> 29:08.460
♪♪

29:08.503 --> 29:11.593
Yeah.

29:11.637 --> 29:13.857
Yeah, if I could do it
all over again...

29:13.900 --> 29:16.598
♪♪

29:16.642 --> 29:18.687
...I'd have killed
every single one of you.

29:18.731 --> 29:27.784
♪♪

29:27.827 --> 29:29.350
♪♪

29:29.394 --> 29:31.700
Why would you
say that?

29:31.744 --> 29:33.311
♪♪

29:33.354 --> 29:36.357
It's the truth.

29:36.401 --> 29:39.143
We got to do
whatever we can

29:39.186 --> 29:40.405
to protect our people,
right?

29:40.448 --> 29:41.710
I mean,
that's why we're here.

29:41.754 --> 29:44.061
That's why
we're doing this.

29:44.104 --> 29:46.411
♪♪

29:46.454 --> 29:48.892
Why would you say that
to me?

29:48.935 --> 29:56.595
♪♪

29:56.638 --> 30:00.251
We had a good day,
you and I.

30:00.294 --> 30:05.560
And the only way this works,
Maggie, is --

30:05.604 --> 30:07.736
is if
we're honest.

30:07.780 --> 30:16.789
♪♪

30:16.833 --> 30:18.182
♪♪

30:18.225 --> 30:19.400
Where do they bring these,
exactly?

30:19.444 --> 30:20.880
[Grunts]

30:20.924 --> 30:22.751
Uh, I don't know.

30:22.795 --> 30:25.580
Somewhere far from the fields
and the water supply.

30:25.624 --> 30:27.887
Ezekiel: Friends!

30:27.931 --> 30:30.672
[Laughs]
Much gratitude.

30:30.716 --> 30:33.110
I see you've done
all my work for me.

30:33.153 --> 30:35.547
And I didn't even
bring you lollipops.

30:35.590 --> 30:37.157
Wait.

30:37.201 --> 30:40.726
Ha! [Laughs]

30:40.769 --> 30:42.597
You don't want one?

30:42.641 --> 30:44.469
Oh, I have had several.
[Chuckles]

30:44.512 --> 30:46.950
So, how was it?
Good as new.

30:46.993 --> 30:50.170
I got antibiotics,
painkillers, IV fluids.

30:52.738 --> 30:54.609
Thank you,
truly, friend.

30:54.653 --> 30:56.089
Happy to do it.

30:56.133 --> 30:58.135
Glad everyone's okay.
[Chuckles]

30:58.178 --> 31:00.528
You feel up to
a new assignment or --

31:00.572 --> 31:02.356
Yes!

31:04.402 --> 31:06.795
Bring it on.

31:06.839 --> 31:08.972
Stephanie, Eugene,

31:09.015 --> 31:11.931
I'd like you to clear the area
up along the north fence line.

31:11.975 --> 31:13.802
Can you show him?
Yeah, sure.

31:13.846 --> 31:15.326
Excellent.

31:15.369 --> 31:17.981
Ezekiel, Princess,
come with me.

31:18.024 --> 31:26.293
♪♪

31:26.337 --> 31:29.601
[Walkers growling]

31:29.644 --> 31:33.648
♪♪

31:33.692 --> 31:35.824
Gabriel: Maggie.

31:35.868 --> 31:38.218
♪♪

31:38.262 --> 31:40.655
Good news.

31:40.699 --> 31:42.309
It's still there.

31:42.353 --> 31:44.398
You run into
any of them?

31:44.442 --> 31:46.400
No.

31:46.444 --> 31:49.099
♪♪

31:49.142 --> 31:52.363
[Growling continues]

31:52.406 --> 32:02.373
♪♪

32:02.416 --> 32:04.027
♪♪

32:04.070 --> 32:05.637
That looks good
over there.

32:05.680 --> 32:11.991
♪♪

32:12.035 --> 32:15.995
[Walkers growling]

32:16.039 --> 32:18.476
Come on, man.

32:18.519 --> 32:20.652
♪♪

32:20.695 --> 32:22.871
I got this one.

32:22.915 --> 32:28.007
♪♪

32:28.051 --> 32:29.966
Eugene!

32:30.009 --> 32:39.976
♪♪

32:40.019 --> 32:41.542
♪♪

32:41.586 --> 32:44.110
Thanks, partner.

32:44.154 --> 32:45.329
Teamwork is all.

32:45.372 --> 32:48.375
Yeah.

32:48.419 --> 32:50.377
What the hell
was that about?

32:50.421 --> 32:52.466
You just
disrupted our date.

32:52.510 --> 32:54.033
Excuse me.

32:54.077 --> 32:55.600
We just
saved your life.

32:55.643 --> 32:57.732
We have private security
for that.

32:57.776 --> 32:59.256
Eugene, let's go.

32:59.299 --> 33:01.040
They're -- You know what?
Best idea yet.

33:01.084 --> 33:03.477
Well, there's no reason
to be so rude, hoss.

33:03.521 --> 33:04.783
[Chuckles] Hoss?

33:04.826 --> 33:06.611
Oh, my God.
Sorry.

33:06.654 --> 33:08.047
I'm just not used to talking
to a plebeian, so this is --

33:08.091 --> 33:09.309
Oh, someone used
their dictionary.

33:09.353 --> 33:11.311
Hey, Eugene.Now, just a minute.

33:11.355 --> 33:12.791
We have earned either gratitude
or an apology,

33:12.834 --> 33:14.575
whichever this young man
can muster first.

33:14.619 --> 33:16.534
Eugene.Who the hell do you think
that you are?

33:16.577 --> 33:17.970
I think I'm talking to someone
who's being

33:18.014 --> 33:19.189
extremely rude
right now.Eugene.

33:19.232 --> 33:21.060
Now just hold your horses
one second.

33:21.104 --> 33:22.931
You have no idea
who you're talking to right now.Eugene.

33:22.975 --> 33:24.759
Oh, I think I do, and that would
be a tiny, little man.

33:24.803 --> 33:26.718
You're so smart.

33:26.761 --> 33:28.415
♪♪

33:28.459 --> 33:31.244
[Screams]

33:31.288 --> 33:33.681
You stupid bitch!

33:33.725 --> 33:35.683
Look what you just did
to my girlfriend!

33:35.727 --> 33:37.163
♪♪

33:37.207 --> 33:38.817
[Groans]

33:38.860 --> 33:41.037
Oh, my God!
What did you do?!

33:41.080 --> 33:43.169
This guy was being,
well, an asshole.

33:43.213 --> 33:45.258
Look, we're --
we're so sorry.No, don't touch!

33:45.302 --> 33:46.564
We've been working
without a break,

33:46.607 --> 33:49.349
and he didn't mean to.

33:49.393 --> 33:51.656
What the hell
happened here?

33:51.699 --> 33:54.006
Look what they did
to Kayla.

33:54.050 --> 33:56.313
These lunatics
attacked us.

33:56.356 --> 33:58.619
You know, this is
all yourfault, Mercer.

33:58.663 --> 34:00.273
Where the hell
were you?!

34:00.317 --> 34:03.363
I had goddamn rotters
up my ass!

34:03.407 --> 34:07.019
And then this dumb shit
rolled up and attacked me.

34:07.063 --> 34:09.065
That is
categorically untrue.

34:09.108 --> 34:11.067
Did you hit him?

34:11.110 --> 34:14.026
Yes, but --What the hell
were you thinking?

34:14.070 --> 34:15.984
Don't you know
who that is?

34:16.028 --> 34:24.167
♪♪

34:25.690 --> 34:28.127
Hi.
I'm Yumiko Okumura.

34:28.171 --> 34:30.477
I'm here for my meeting
with Ms. Milton.

34:30.521 --> 34:32.349
Thank you
for being on time.

34:32.392 --> 34:34.873
Ms. Milton is fastidious
about her schedule.

34:34.916 --> 34:37.441
Would you like
an herbal tea?

34:37.484 --> 34:39.138
No, thank you.

34:39.182 --> 34:41.140
Sparkling water
or espresso?

34:41.184 --> 34:43.447
No.
I'm alright.

34:43.490 --> 34:45.362
Please,
have a seat.

35:03.597 --> 35:13.564
♪♪

35:13.607 --> 35:21.398
♪♪

35:21.441 --> 35:24.270
You're part of the new group
that came in, right?

35:24.314 --> 35:27.099
♪♪

35:27.143 --> 35:28.405
Yeah.

35:28.448 --> 35:30.146
I guess.

35:30.189 --> 35:32.931
Are you all
settling in okay?Yeah.

35:32.974 --> 35:37.414
I mean, I haven't seen
my friends in a few days, so...

35:37.457 --> 35:39.938
♪♪

35:39.981 --> 35:42.897
Oh.
I'm sorry to hear that.

35:42.941 --> 35:44.986
Is everyone okay?

35:45.030 --> 35:47.032
[Telephone rings]

35:47.075 --> 35:49.077
Yes?

35:51.167 --> 35:52.516
Yes.
Of course.

35:52.559 --> 35:54.431
I'll -- I'll do it now.

35:54.474 --> 35:56.955
♪♪

35:56.998 --> 35:58.609
Is everything okay?

35:58.652 --> 36:01.177
I'm afraid Ms. Milton
will have to reschedule.

36:01.220 --> 36:03.266
Someone just
attacked her son.

36:03.309 --> 36:05.006
♪♪

36:10.098 --> 36:19.630
♪♪

36:19.673 --> 36:20.892
♪♪

36:20.935 --> 36:23.373
[Door opens]

36:23.416 --> 36:29.683
♪♪

36:31.555 --> 36:33.513
[Chuckles]

36:33.557 --> 36:35.341
Situation like that,

36:35.385 --> 36:37.996
you're supposed to
save him,

36:38.039 --> 36:39.389
protect
the governor's son.

36:39.432 --> 36:41.608
You'd have been
a hero.

36:41.652 --> 36:43.871
You could have asked
for anything.

36:43.915 --> 36:45.351
My apologies.

36:45.395 --> 36:48.136
I did not ascertain
such a conclusion.

36:50.095 --> 36:51.879
Alright, no more
screwing around.

36:55.187 --> 36:56.928
You want out,

36:56.971 --> 37:00.105
now the price
is higher.

37:00.148 --> 37:02.238
I need the name of your town
and how to get there.

37:02.281 --> 37:04.501
T-That is beyond
my purview.

37:07.199 --> 37:09.941
Then welcome.

37:09.984 --> 37:12.900
This is home.

37:12.944 --> 37:15.468
Your friends can
keep killing walkers.

37:15.512 --> 37:16.861
Your people,
wherever they are,

37:16.904 --> 37:20.952
can figure things out
on their own.

37:28.394 --> 37:31.092
I-If I were to disclose
those coordinates,

37:31.136 --> 37:32.659
what guarantee
could you provide

37:32.703 --> 37:34.966
for my
community's safety?

37:35.009 --> 37:36.402
Look around.

37:36.446 --> 37:38.883
Think how
we've treated you.

37:38.926 --> 37:41.102
All the chances
you've gotten.

37:41.146 --> 37:43.409
That's not a directly reply
to my query.

37:47.021 --> 37:48.371
Up to you.

37:50.895 --> 37:54.986
[Door opens]

37:55.029 --> 37:56.988
Wait.

37:57.031 --> 38:03.516
♪♪

38:03.560 --> 38:06.824
[Walkers growling]

38:06.867 --> 38:16.834
♪♪

38:16.877 --> 38:26.844
♪♪

38:26.887 --> 38:36.854
♪♪

38:36.897 --> 38:46.864
♪♪

38:46.907 --> 38:56.874
♪♪

38:56.917 --> 39:06.884
♪♪

39:06.927 --> 39:09.408
♪♪

39:09.452 --> 39:12.672
[Walkers growling]

39:12.716 --> 39:22.682
♪♪

39:22.726 --> 39:32.692
♪♪

39:32.736 --> 39:35.303
♪♪

39:35.347 --> 39:40.570
[Thunder rumbles]

39:42.746 --> 39:45.749
[Door creaks]

39:58.370 --> 40:08.336
♪♪

40:08.380 --> 40:18.346
♪♪

40:18.390 --> 40:23.569
♪♪

40:23.613 --> 40:25.789
See?

40:25.832 --> 40:29.183
I told you
the truth.

40:29.227 --> 40:31.185
Please don't hurt us.

40:31.229 --> 40:33.840
[Thunder rumbles]

40:33.884 --> 40:39.063
♪♪

40:39.106 --> 40:42.675
You need to take
your son and run.

40:42.719 --> 40:44.503
Don't ever
come back here.

40:44.547 --> 40:49.769
♪♪

40:49.813 --> 40:52.380
Go with your dad.

40:52.424 --> 40:54.295
Go ahead, honey.

40:54.339 --> 40:55.514
Don't be afraid.

40:55.558 --> 40:57.168
It's okay.

40:57.211 --> 41:02.565
♪♪

41:02.608 --> 41:06.612
[Crying]

41:06.656 --> 41:08.396
I love you.

41:08.440 --> 41:10.834
I love you.

41:10.877 --> 41:12.139
Go.

41:12.183 --> 41:19.320
♪♪

41:19.364 --> 41:21.061
[Sighs]

41:21.105 --> 41:24.848
Oh, thank God
for you.

41:24.891 --> 41:27.415
He answered
my prayers.

41:27.459 --> 41:30.854
They were never gonna leave
while I was still alive,

41:30.897 --> 41:33.160
and it was dangerous
for them to stay.

41:33.204 --> 41:37.208
♪♪

41:37.251 --> 41:39.210
I'm ready.

41:39.253 --> 41:42.169
♪♪

41:42.213 --> 41:44.432
Please.

41:44.476 --> 41:51.831
♪♪

41:51.875 --> 41:56.575
[Thunder rumbles]

41:56.619 --> 42:01.885
♪♪

42:10.458 --> 42:14.114
♪♪

42:14.158 --> 42:16.813
What are you
gonna tell Pope?

42:16.856 --> 42:19.729
♪♪

42:19.772 --> 42:21.731
That you killed them.

42:21.774 --> 42:23.646
It'll be good
for you.

42:23.689 --> 42:33.656
♪♪

42:33.699 --> 42:43.666
♪♪

42:43.709 --> 42:46.059
♪♪

42:46.103 --> 42:49.541
Look, Leah, there's something
I need to tell you.

42:49.585 --> 42:51.717
Man:
Come in, Shaw.

42:51.761 --> 42:54.111
Shaw. Over.

42:54.154 --> 42:55.721
We need you back ASAP.

42:55.765 --> 42:59.116
We gotta go.

42:59.159 --> 43:02.641
♪♪

43:02.685 --> 43:07.864
[Thunder rumbles]

43:07.907 --> 43:11.171
[Walkers growling]

43:11.215 --> 43:21.181
♪♪

43:21.225 --> 43:31.191
♪♪

43:31.235 --> 43:41.201
♪♪

43:41.245 --> 43:47.120
♪♪

43:47.164 --> 43:50.428
[Crying softly]

43:50.471 --> 44:00.438
♪♪

44:00.481 --> 44:10.448
♪♪

44:10.491 --> 44:20.458
♪♪

44:20.501 --> 44:28.466
♪♪

44:28.509 --> 44:37.301
♪♪

44:40.565 --> 44:44.221
♪♪

44:44.264 --> 44:46.571
I'll tell you what.

44:46.614 --> 44:49.443
You make me a promise
in front of the goddamn priest,

44:49.487 --> 44:51.097
and I will stick around.

44:51.141 --> 44:52.838
Promise you what?

44:52.882 --> 44:55.493
I do this for you,
then we're even, we are good.

44:55.536 --> 44:58.757
I don't have to keep
looking over my shoulder.

44:58.801 --> 45:02.152
I think that Negan feels

45:02.195 --> 45:05.372
that as much as
he doesn't trust Maggie,

45:05.416 --> 45:08.419
as much as he feels
that she hates him

45:08.462 --> 45:11.639
and wishes him ill,
I do think he senses

45:11.683 --> 45:13.772
that she's a straight shooter
in some ways.

45:13.816 --> 45:16.122
There's an aspect to Negan
that's like that, too.

45:16.166 --> 45:18.734
I mean, like, Negan is
a tricky individual,

45:18.777 --> 45:21.693
but you can't really say
that he's much of a liar.

45:21.737 --> 45:24.957
You kind of wish, "Man, if they
could only see eye-to-eye,

45:25.001 --> 45:27.525
they could actually be
a very, very powerful team.

45:27.568 --> 45:29.440
But you understand
why they don't, of course.

45:31.137 --> 45:33.009
The interesting thing is,
Maggie's, like,

45:33.052 --> 45:35.489
kind of response to him
asking for a promise

45:35.533 --> 45:39.145
is just to kind of look at him
and be almost, like, amused

45:39.189 --> 45:42.496
darkly about the fact that he'd
take a promise from her.

45:42.540 --> 45:45.412
♪♪

45:45.456 --> 45:47.893
Negan used to be a gym teacher.

45:47.937 --> 45:49.939
He's always had this kind of
patience with children.

45:49.982 --> 45:51.636
I think he likes to teach.

45:51.679 --> 45:54.378
You ready?This is not fun.

45:54.421 --> 45:56.423
Well, not with
that attitude.

45:56.467 --> 45:58.730
If you really think about,
like, what he's doing

45:58.774 --> 46:00.688
when he's monologuing
all the time,

46:00.732 --> 46:02.778
you wonder who's the villain.
He was trying to teach people

46:02.821 --> 46:05.215
about his philosophy
of the world.

46:05.258 --> 46:08.435
For us, as writers, it makes
all the sense in the world

46:08.479 --> 46:10.960
that he would actually be
a pretty decent coach

46:11.003 --> 46:12.962
and know how to
sort of, like, motivate

46:13.005 --> 46:14.354
and be like,
"You're doing great,"

46:14.398 --> 46:15.878
because I actually think

46:15.921 --> 46:18.141
that is pretty fundamental
to who he is.

46:18.184 --> 46:20.186
You did good, Maggie.

46:20.230 --> 46:23.973
Maggie hates that she needs
Negan to help her with anything.

46:24.016 --> 46:26.584
She's used to being good
at what she does,

46:26.627 --> 46:28.934
and she certainly doesn't like
to be bad at what she does

46:28.978 --> 46:30.893
in front of him.

46:30.936 --> 46:35.158
One of my favorite scenes is
the scene where Maggie and Negan

46:35.201 --> 46:37.725
talk about what happened
in the past,

46:37.769 --> 46:39.510
kind of where they are now.

46:39.553 --> 46:42.774
Negan brings up the attack
in the satellite station

46:42.818 --> 46:45.690
wiping out this entire
group of Saviors.

46:45.733 --> 46:48.954
We know that those Saviors
were doing bad things

46:48.998 --> 46:50.695
and they were doing harm
to people,

46:50.738 --> 46:53.524
but at the same time,
to our characters,

46:53.567 --> 46:55.221
what's interesting is, like,
these were just

46:55.265 --> 46:57.006
nameless, faceless people
that they felt like

46:57.049 --> 46:58.355
they could go in and kill.

46:58.398 --> 47:00.357
And I think,
from Negan's perspective,

47:00.400 --> 47:02.228
those were people that wanted
to live their lives.

47:02.272 --> 47:04.927
Like, they had families.
There was that baby Gracie.

47:04.970 --> 47:07.320
Once you start,
like, looking at it

47:07.364 --> 47:11.063
and flip the view,
it does change some things.

47:11.107 --> 47:14.110
They were still human beings
that lost their lives in that.

47:14.153 --> 47:17.200
One of the things that we always
try to remember in the show is

47:17.243 --> 47:20.899
that with any villain,
there is still a humanity there.

47:20.943 --> 47:23.946
There's still a person
at the bottom of it all.

47:23.989 --> 47:25.730
It can be
a very, very evil person,

47:25.773 --> 47:27.123
but there's still a person,

47:27.166 --> 47:29.125
and they're connected
to other people,

47:29.168 --> 47:31.344
who, for whatever reason,
have decided

47:31.388 --> 47:34.304
that this is the best path
to go down.

47:34.347 --> 47:36.872
We did talk about, like,

47:36.915 --> 47:40.701
"Does Negan regret
what he did with Glenn?"

47:40.745 --> 47:44.096
Like, "Does he regret that?"
And I don't think he does.

47:44.140 --> 47:46.882
I think he thinks that was
the right strategic move.

47:46.925 --> 47:48.753
Yeah, if I could do it
all over again,

47:48.796 --> 47:51.974
I'd have killed
every single one of you.

47:52.017 --> 47:56.239
If he's thinking of, "How could
I have preserved what I had?"

47:56.282 --> 47:57.718
he should have
wiped them all out.

47:57.762 --> 48:00.025
His problem was,
he kept liking them

48:00.069 --> 48:02.375
and not wanting to kill more.

48:02.419 --> 48:04.812
So, if he had wanted
to win that war,

48:04.856 --> 48:07.206
he probably should have wiped
out everybody in that line,

48:07.250 --> 48:10.166
because they were all leaders
who rose up against him.

48:10.209 --> 48:13.299
And that's
a very, very dark position,

48:13.343 --> 48:17.086
but at the same time, you know,
as they're on the brink

48:17.129 --> 48:19.784
of going in against these people
and they're talking about,

48:19.827 --> 48:21.829
"Do we just sneak in
and take the food?

48:21.873 --> 48:23.962
Or do we have to
do something more?"

48:24.006 --> 48:27.226
he's kind of saying,
"Let's be real here

48:27.270 --> 48:29.533
about what we're talking about
on this mission."

48:29.576 --> 48:31.752
You are about to do
some crazy shit

48:31.796 --> 48:35.017
and break into a community
that you built and lost.

48:35.060 --> 48:38.107
[Birds chirping]I get it.

48:38.150 --> 48:39.717
♪♪

48:39.760 --> 48:41.588
One of the themes
we've been dealing with,

48:41.632 --> 48:45.201
with Father Gabriel, is just
his relationship to faith

48:45.244 --> 48:46.898
over the course of years.

48:46.942 --> 48:48.378
And I think one of the things

48:48.421 --> 48:50.815
that we've really held on
to with him

48:50.858 --> 48:54.123
is that he continues
to wear that collar.

48:54.166 --> 48:57.996
Even during times
when things are terrible,

48:58.040 --> 49:00.216
he has tried and tried
to hold on to his faith.

49:00.259 --> 49:01.957
But he's definitely been feeling

49:02.000 --> 49:04.046
like he doesn't hear God
anymore.

49:04.089 --> 49:05.873
It's something that bothers him.

49:05.917 --> 49:09.399
And I just thought it was
really interesting,

49:09.442 --> 49:12.445
as we were talking about
this sort of religious figure

49:12.489 --> 49:14.665
that would be embedded
with the Reapers,

49:14.708 --> 49:18.016
and they have their own
interpretation of religion,

49:18.060 --> 49:21.498
we wanted to deal with a group
that has a very particular way

49:21.541 --> 49:23.369
in which they feel
that they are chosen

49:23.413 --> 49:24.805
and what they choose
to do with it.

49:24.849 --> 49:28.418
And I think, for Gabriel,
who is struggling

49:28.461 --> 49:31.725
and trying to find
that feeling he once felt

49:31.769 --> 49:35.642
when he was just sort of
a young priest starting out,

49:35.686 --> 49:38.994
he's definitely taken aback
by seeing this person

49:39.037 --> 49:43.520
who seems to be just actively
talking to God

49:43.563 --> 49:46.871
and at least is acting
like he hears God's voice.

49:46.914 --> 49:48.655
And what does that mean
to Gabriel?

49:48.699 --> 49:51.745
And it almost feels like a sign
to him in some way.

49:51.789 --> 49:54.313
You have guided me through
the darkest of times.

49:54.357 --> 49:56.576
I treasure
our conversation

49:56.620 --> 49:58.535
and the guidance
you have given me.

49:58.578 --> 50:00.885
Thank you, Father.

50:00.928 --> 50:04.149
One of the things we wanted
to show in this story

50:04.193 --> 50:07.109
is that Leah -- she is
an independent thinker.

50:07.152 --> 50:09.372
I think she's used to
following orders,

50:09.415 --> 50:12.070
and we know
that she feels like Pope

50:12.114 --> 50:15.030
gave her the family
that she has

50:15.073 --> 50:17.380
and believed in her when
nobody else believed in her.

50:17.423 --> 50:19.773
And we think
that's really important.

50:19.817 --> 50:21.906
And so she has
this loyalty to him.

50:21.949 --> 50:24.343
And I think, in some ways,
like, this is a story

50:24.387 --> 50:26.432
of the frog boiling in a pot.

50:26.476 --> 50:30.175
The water has just gotten slowly
hotter and hotter over time.

50:30.219 --> 50:33.396
And your sense of
what is normal and acceptable,

50:33.439 --> 50:35.441
like, the line
just starts to move.

50:35.485 --> 50:37.661
But it moves so slowly
that you don't notice it

50:37.704 --> 50:41.752
until, suddenly, like, the guy's
locking you in a burning room,

50:41.795 --> 50:43.928
and you're like,
"That seems off, right?"

50:43.971 --> 50:46.931
And I think, like,
Daryl is right there,

50:46.974 --> 50:50.543
trying to feel out, like,
"Is that the real you?"

50:50.587 --> 50:52.632
Like, "Does this feel like
normal behavior to you?"

50:52.676 --> 50:56.810
And I think, like, in that way,
he's testing her and seeing,

50:56.854 --> 50:59.770
like, whether's she somebody
that could help him in this.

50:59.813 --> 51:01.337
And he doesn't know.

51:01.380 --> 51:02.947
Like, he's trying
to work it all out.

51:02.990 --> 51:05.689
I don't think he has
a whole lot of trust in her

51:05.732 --> 51:08.213
at this point,
since she's with this group.

51:08.257 --> 51:11.129
But they come across
this young father,

51:11.173 --> 51:13.697
and Leah has this very
just sort of, like,

51:13.740 --> 51:15.568
emotional reaction to it.

51:15.612 --> 51:18.223
And she defies Pope's order
to kill them.

51:18.267 --> 51:19.877
You need to take your son
and run.

51:19.920 --> 51:22.271
Don't ever come back here.

51:22.314 --> 51:25.012
In that moment, Daryl
is starting to see

51:25.056 --> 51:27.363
that he was not wrong.

51:27.406 --> 51:30.409
She does still have
this emotional core --

51:30.453 --> 51:33.630
the part of her
that he thought was sweet

51:33.673 --> 51:36.154
and cared about
protecting people.

51:36.198 --> 51:38.287
I think he's looking
for those clues

51:38.330 --> 51:40.419
that tell him whether or not

51:40.463 --> 51:42.508
he can bring her in
on what he's doing.

51:42.552 --> 51:45.381
♪♪

51:45.424 --> 51:47.513
[Sighs]

51:47.557 --> 51:52.214
♪♪

51:54.607 --> 52:04.530
♪♪

52:04.574 --> 52:14.540
♪♪

